    <stitle>CAB: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - DOOR VENT WINDOW AND FRONT RUN CHANNEL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
        <title>DOOR VENT WINDOW AND FRONT RUN CHANNEL</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1600734">Figure 34</hotlnk>for Items in parentheses.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1600734" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1600734" filename="../figg16/G1600734.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 34. Door Vent Window and Front Run Channel</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. VENT WINDOW</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. FRONT RUN CHANNEL</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. PAN HEAD MOUNTING SCREW</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The door vent window (Item 1) and front run channel (Item 2) are serviced as one assembly. It is held
                in place in the door by two pan head screws and two hex head bolts.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cab door glass. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16007s_25.xml" xrefid="x1600708">CAB DOOR GLASS, Remove</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">At the outside of the door, remove two pan head mounting screws (Item 3), one from top
                    and one from front edge of window frame.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">From inside of door, remove two hex head bolts and remove vent window and front run
                    channel (Items 1 and 2) from door.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift out vent window and front run channel (Items 1 and 2) as an assembly through window
                    frame.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide vent window and front run channel (Items 1 and 2) in position as an assembly. From
                    inside door, secure front run channel with two hex head bolts. Tighten until snug.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure vent window with the pan head mounting screws (Item 3) to top and front edge of
                    window frame.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install cab door glass. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16007s_25.xml" xrefid="x1600709">CAB DOOR GLASS, Install</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
